WEBVTT

00:09.242 --> 00:10.242
Did you give
that to her?

00:10.244 --> 00:11.710
Hands behind
your back, please.

00:11.712 --> 00:12.511
Bird, tell them.

00:12.513 --> 00:14.246
I'm here to
pick up Carter--
No, Liz.

00:14.248 --> 00:16.582
Crash came by.
Some idiot clerk

00:16.584 --> 00:18.517
allowed him to post
bail for her.

00:18.519 --> 00:19.785
She left with him?

00:19.787 --> 00:20.619
Whoo!

00:20.621 --> 00:21.687
So where are we going?

00:21.689 --> 00:22.821
Where do you
wanna go?

00:22.823 --> 00:24.823
Somewhere where
nobody knows me.

00:24.825 --> 00:25.758
(phone beeping)

00:25.760 --> 00:27.226
Oh, my God.
What?

00:27.228 --> 00:29.795
Elizabeth put out
an AMBER Alert?

00:29.797 --> 00:31.230
Dammit.

00:31.232 --> 00:32.364
I wish everyone
in the world

00:32.366 --> 00:33.532
wasn't looking
for us right now.

00:33.534 --> 00:35.334
Wait, everybody is
looking for us.

00:35.336 --> 00:37.202
My mom would have seen
the AMBER Alert.

00:37.204 --> 00:41.340
We need to go leave a
message for her with Max.

00:41.342 --> 00:43.409
Why did you buy that?

00:43.411 --> 00:44.843
Oh, yeah.

00:44.845 --> 00:47.379
I knew you'd
come back.

00:47.381 --> 00:49.481
Will you give that
to her if you see her?

00:49.483 --> 00:51.183
(Crash)
Max, you wanna
help us, right?

00:51.185 --> 00:53.886
Well, I mean, I know
you wanna help Carter.

00:53.888 --> 00:55.854
Give us everything
in your register.

00:55.856 --> 00:56.889
Report it as a robbery.

00:56.891 --> 00:58.557
Crash, what the hell
are you doing?

00:58.559 --> 01:00.359
The safety's on, see?

01:00.361 --> 01:01.593
(gunshot)

01:01.595 --> 01:02.861
Call 9-1-1!

01:02.863 --> 01:04.530
Max, my God.

01:04.532 --> 01:05.764
Oh, God.

01:05.766 --> 01:07.499
(Carter)
Help me.

01:07.501 --> 01:09.134
What were you doing
with a gun?

01:09.136 --> 01:10.369
(Taylor)
I don't know what's worse,

01:10.371 --> 01:12.838
you being abducted or
you coming back here.

01:12.840 --> 01:15.174
No, I will never
forgive you.

01:15.176 --> 01:19.378
Girls, the doctor
has asked to see us.

01:22.749 --> 01:25.984
do we
have covering that?

01:27.353 --> 01:28.420
Is he all right?

01:28.422 --> 01:29.922
When can he come home?

01:29.924 --> 01:31.056
How did it go?

01:31.058 --> 01:32.357
He came through
the surgery.

01:32.359 --> 01:34.960
He's very fortunate that the
wound was a through and through.

01:34.962 --> 01:36.929
It could've been
much worse.

01:36.931 --> 01:38.263
Well, can we see him
at least?

01:38.265 --> 01:41.934
Currently Max is
non-responsive.

01:41.936 --> 01:43.802
Nonre-- what does
that mean?

01:43.804 --> 01:44.903
Is that a coma?

01:44.905 --> 01:45.704
Hopefully.

01:45.706 --> 01:46.705
Hopefully,
it's a coma?

01:46.707 --> 01:48.407
If it's a coma,
he can wake up.

01:48.409 --> 01:52.311
When someone's just
non-responsive...

01:52.313 --> 01:54.413
At this point,
we're in a waiting game.

01:54.415 --> 01:56.782
The best thing you can
all do is just go home

01:56.784 --> 01:57.683
and get some rest.

01:57.685 --> 01:59.051
My staff and I will be
in touch with you.

01:59.053 --> 02:00.886
Oh, but please,
please.

02:00.888 --> 02:03.222
Look, surely, he's more
likely to wake up

02:03.224 --> 02:05.991
if he hears
voices he recognizes.

02:05.993 --> 02:08.494
Please, can we see him?

02:10.063 --> 02:11.029
All right, fine.

02:11.031 --> 02:13.799
One person
for one minute.

02:15.835 --> 02:18.137
Carter!

02:22.942 --> 02:25.177
(door closing)

02:26.980 --> 02:29.815
(woman over P.A.)
<i>Radiology, line four.</i>

02:29.817 --> 02:33.152
<i>Radiology, line four.</i>

02:39.792 --> 02:42.327
(monitor beeping)

02:55.341 --> 02:57.009
Max.

02:59.112 --> 03:01.180
Max, it's me.

03:06.219 --> 03:09.354
I'm so sorry.

03:09.356 --> 03:12.357
I am so sorry.

03:17.230 --> 03:20.098
I'm gonna make
things right.

03:20.100 --> 03:22.401
I promise.

03:22.403 --> 03:25.037
But Max, you have
to wake up.

03:27.907 --> 03:32.144
You have to wake up
for me to do that.

03:36.749 --> 03:39.084
♪ There you go

03:39.086 --> 03:41.720
♪ There
you stay ♪

03:41.722 --> 03:43.322
♪ Keeping low

03:43.324 --> 03:45.424
♪ Never wanna play

03:45.426 --> 03:48.193
♪ You've been
up and down, down ♪

03:48.195 --> 03:51.096
♪ You've been low
low, low ♪

03:51.098 --> 03:55.867
♪ Pretending
to not feel alone ♪

03:55.869 --> 04:00.872
♪ Pretending to not
feel alone ♪

04:03.142 --> 04:05.043
(Elizabeth)
I really wanna
come back to work.

04:05.045 --> 04:07.879
You need me for this
Mini-Mart shooting.

04:07.881 --> 04:10.082
I know the suspect
better than anyone else.

04:10.084 --> 04:13.819
Sir, this kid, he's a
flight risk.

04:13.821 --> 04:16.722
And we're gonna lose him.

04:16.724 --> 04:19.891
I can get him.

04:19.893 --> 04:22.828
Just give me
a chance.

04:24.130 --> 04:27.833
Pick up your badge
and your revolver.

04:28.835 --> 04:31.937
♪ I feel it
when I can't sleep ♪

04:31.939 --> 04:35.340
♪ The reason that
I want to eat it ♪

04:35.342 --> 04:40.279
♪ How I ended up
on the floor ♪

04:41.881 --> 04:43.982
(sighs)
Hey.

04:43.984 --> 04:47.019
Was last night
just a bad dream?

04:47.021 --> 04:50.422
♪ The only thing I want
now is you ♪

04:50.424 --> 04:52.157
No.

04:53.092 --> 04:56.762
♪ I can see
it all so clear... ♪

04:56.764 --> 04:57.996
Grant.

04:57.998 --> 05:02.234
♪ I am lost
without ♪

05:02.236 --> 05:05.070
♪ You here

05:05.072 --> 05:08.073
♪ So lost

05:11.411 --> 05:14.946
♪ Without you

05:15.381 --> 05:19.985
I know you're not
talking to me right now.

05:26.359 --> 05:30.462
I know you've got much bigger
things on your mind, but...

05:30.464 --> 05:33.832
this stuff
with Max...

05:33.834 --> 05:36.101
Life is short.

05:39.172 --> 05:41.306
I'm gonna do
everything I can

05:41.308 --> 05:43.208
to make it right
between us.

05:43.210 --> 05:44.810
(door opening)

05:44.812 --> 05:46.712
Hey.

05:46.714 --> 05:48.380
Hi.

05:48.382 --> 05:51.350
Figured you'd be
needing that.

05:56.189 --> 05:57.756
Same number.

05:57.758 --> 05:59.791
Thank you.

05:59.793 --> 06:02.828
You're dressed up.

06:02.830 --> 06:04.162
Job interview.

06:04.164 --> 06:05.163
What kind of
interview?

06:05.165 --> 06:07.999
Teaching literature
and essay writing

06:08.001 --> 06:12.137
to tenth graders at the
McAllister Holt Academy.

06:12.139 --> 06:13.772
You already have a job,
you're a writer.

06:13.774 --> 06:16.241
This might be better,
don't you think?

06:16.243 --> 06:18.343
Than being a writer?

06:18.345 --> 06:19.411
No.

06:19.413 --> 06:20.912
I know it comes
at a terrible time.

06:20.914 --> 06:23.248
I can easily cancel if
you think I should.

06:23.250 --> 06:26.885
No, no, I don't want you
to miss out on this.

06:26.887 --> 06:29.020
Wish me luck.

06:31.224 --> 06:32.391
David?

06:32.393 --> 06:34.860
Good luck.

06:36.763 --> 06:40.232
See you, bud.

06:40.234 --> 06:41.867
Hey.
Hi.

06:41.869 --> 06:42.634
Where you going?

06:42.636 --> 06:45.937
I'm going to stay at the
hospital until Max wakes up.

06:45.939 --> 06:48.039
I wanna be the first
person he sees

06:48.041 --> 06:49.241
when he opens his eyes.

06:49.243 --> 06:51.777
Taylor, I'm sorry
about earlier.

06:51.779 --> 06:52.944
I just didn't think.

06:52.946 --> 06:54.413
But, honestly, there is
no way in hell

06:54.415 --> 06:56.047
he even knew
I was in the room.

06:56.049 --> 06:56.915
Yeah, but I did.

06:56.917 --> 06:59.918
I know you love Max,
but he is also my best

06:59.920 --> 07:02.120
and oldest friend in
the entire world.

07:02.122 --> 07:03.722
If you care about
Max so much,

07:03.724 --> 07:05.023
why don't you devote
your time to finding

07:05.025 --> 07:07.993
your fugitive boyfriend
and getting him arrested?

07:07.995 --> 07:09.261
This is giving
me a headache.

07:09.263 --> 07:11.963
Okay, all right,
the last thing that we need

07:11.965 --> 07:14.065
is the two of you going
at each other.

07:14.067 --> 07:15.300
Don't worry,
I'm leaving.

07:15.302 --> 07:18.670
Carter can find someone
else to fight with.

07:18.672 --> 07:21.440
She always does.

07:21.442 --> 07:24.676
(door opening
and closing)

07:24.678 --> 07:26.845
Look...

07:26.847 --> 07:30.382
There is something else
that I need to tell you.

07:30.384 --> 07:31.416
What?

07:31.418 --> 07:33.618
This morning, I went
down to the station,

07:33.620 --> 07:35.353
I talked to my captain.

07:35.355 --> 07:36.221
Okay.

07:36.223 --> 07:42.027
I am part of the team that is
assigned to apprehend Crash.

07:45.631 --> 07:46.798
Now if Max dies...

07:46.800 --> 07:47.666
Oh, my God, please--

07:47.668 --> 07:51.803
If Max dies,
that's felony murder.

07:51.805 --> 07:53.805
He didn't mean
to shoot him.

07:53.807 --> 07:54.840
I told you,
he thought

07:54.842 --> 07:56.408
the safety was on,
it was an accident.

07:56.410 --> 07:59.377
I saw the footage from
the security camera.

07:59.379 --> 08:02.647
And he pointed
his gun at Max.

08:02.649 --> 08:05.250
And did you
watch after?

08:05.252 --> 08:08.653
Crash lost his mind
after that.

08:08.655 --> 08:09.287
Yes, I saw that.

08:09.289 --> 08:12.657
And then I saw
him run away.

08:12.659 --> 08:13.725
Yeah.

08:13.727 --> 08:15.660
That's 'cause he thought
he'd go to prison.

08:15.662 --> 08:18.296
Which is where
he should be.

08:18.298 --> 08:20.165
Carter.

08:20.167 --> 08:22.033
Look at me.

08:25.037 --> 08:26.671
He left you alone

08:26.673 --> 08:29.975
with your best friend
dying in your arms.

08:34.647 --> 08:36.615
(knocking)

08:36.617 --> 08:38.016
I'm busy.

08:38.018 --> 08:40.418
(Bird)
Carter?

08:45.958 --> 08:47.859
What are you doing here?

08:47.861 --> 08:51.696
Crash has been
calling me non-stop.

08:51.698 --> 08:53.131
He wants to see you.

08:53.133 --> 08:57.068
(phone buzzing)

08:57.070 --> 08:59.971
It's him.

09:07.747 --> 09:12.050
(Carter)
Hey, Bird, are you there,
have you talked to her?

09:12.052 --> 09:13.818
Crash?
Hey.

09:13.820 --> 09:15.420
It's so good to
hear your voice.

09:15.422 --> 09:19.024
Don't call me on
Bird's phone again.

09:19.026 --> 09:21.359
I didn't know how else
to reach you.

09:21.361 --> 09:24.229
I have my
old phone back.

09:24.231 --> 09:25.830
Where are you?

09:25.832 --> 09:26.431
Still here.

09:26.433 --> 09:29.801
I didn't mean to shoot Max,
you know that, I--

09:29.803 --> 09:31.970
It was an accident.

09:31.972 --> 09:33.538
Crash.

09:35.107 --> 09:36.107
You just left me there.

09:36.109 --> 09:38.443
I know, I freaked out,
I didn't know what to do.

09:38.445 --> 09:39.444
I didn't know where to go.

09:39.446 --> 09:42.047
You didn't know you should
stay and help me?

09:42.049 --> 09:43.281
<i>I know, I'm sorry.</i>

09:43.283 --> 09:45.417
I'm sorry.

09:45.419 --> 09:48.353
Max is in a coma,
Crash.

09:54.260 --> 09:57.295
Will you see me?

09:59.532 --> 10:01.833
No.

10:05.738 --> 10:09.274
I don't know.

10:09.276 --> 10:14.045
Crash, you have to
turn yourself in.

10:14.047 --> 10:15.347
(sniffling)
I can't.

10:15.349 --> 10:17.115
Yes, you can
and then you can--

10:17.117 --> 10:20.218
you can explain your
side of the story.

10:20.220 --> 10:21.252
Crash, if they
catch you first,

10:21.254 --> 10:23.421
it's not gonna matter if
it was an accident or not.

10:23.423 --> 10:26.024
<i>No, it's not gonna</i>
<i>matter anyway.</i>

10:26.026 --> 10:28.059
I have to go.

10:28.061 --> 10:29.227
I'm gonna leave tonight.

10:29.229 --> 10:32.797
But, promise me you'll
see me before I go.

10:35.201 --> 10:36.901
I can't Crash,
I have to go.

10:36.903 --> 10:38.403
No, no, no,
wait, wait, wait.

10:38.405 --> 10:41.306
<i>Carter, please,</i>
<i>just meet me.</i>

10:46.479 --> 10:49.247
Here, you can go now.

10:49.249 --> 10:50.215
Carter, I'm here.

10:50.217 --> 10:52.083
I know you're upset
about Max.

10:52.085 --> 10:55.120
I'm just trying
to be your friend.

10:55.122 --> 10:58.123
Come on, Bird, I think we
both know you're not that.

10:58.125 --> 11:00.759
If you could just
let me explain myself--

11:00.761 --> 11:01.326
Explain what?

11:01.328 --> 11:02.427
You don't understand
what it was like--

11:02.429 --> 11:07.098
Bird, you didn't wanna get
in trouble with your parents

11:07.100 --> 11:08.366
so you had me sent to jail.

11:08.368 --> 11:12.103
It's a lot more
complicated than that.

11:12.105 --> 11:15.073
Not to me, Bird.

11:18.878 --> 11:20.545
(sniffling)

11:22.748 --> 11:27.819
♪

11:35.461 --> 11:38.897
♪ Heart beats fast

11:38.899 --> 11:43.334
♪ Colors
and promises ♪

11:43.336 --> 11:45.870
♪ How to be
brave ♪

11:45.872 --> 11:47.505
♪ How can I love

11:47.507 --> 11:52.043
♪ When I'm afraid
to fall ♪

11:52.045 --> 11:57.082
♪ But watching
you stand alone ♪

11:57.084 --> 11:59.084
♪ All of my doubt

11:59.086 --> 12:04.756
♪ Suddenly goes away
somehow ♪

12:07.426 --> 12:12.697
I stopped by your place.

12:12.699 --> 12:13.998
I think it's...

12:14.000 --> 12:16.835
good to be surrounded
by familiar things.

12:16.837 --> 12:19.938
♪ Time has brought
your heart to me ♪

12:19.940 --> 12:21.239
Like me.

12:21.241 --> 12:24.476
♪ For a thousand years

12:24.478 --> 12:30.148
♪ I'll love you for
a thousand more ♪

12:30.150 --> 12:32.250
Max?

12:32.252 --> 12:33.718
Oh, my God.

12:33.720 --> 12:35.754
My poor little baby.

12:35.756 --> 12:37.322
Hi, I'm Taylor.

12:37.324 --> 12:39.057
I'm Max's girlfriend.

12:39.059 --> 12:40.959
You must be
Max's mom.

12:40.961 --> 12:41.793
What happened?

12:41.795 --> 12:45.196
I couldn't get a damn
doctor on the phone and--

12:45.198 --> 12:47.398
Who are you again?

12:47.400 --> 12:49.134
I-- I'm Taylor.

12:49.136 --> 12:50.268
Where's Carter?

12:50.270 --> 12:52.303
She's not here because
the doctor said

12:52.305 --> 12:54.005
only one of us could...

12:54.007 --> 12:57.208
be in the room
at a time.

12:58.944 --> 13:01.479
Honey, honey?

13:01.481 --> 13:03.381
I'm here.

13:03.383 --> 13:04.883
Everything's
gonna be okay.

13:04.885 --> 13:07.051
You're gonna feel better
real soon, okay?

13:07.053 --> 13:10.688
I'll be in the waiting room
if you need me.

13:10.690 --> 13:15.794
The police said that
her boyfriend shot him?

13:15.796 --> 13:17.328
Why, I--

13:18.464 --> 13:21.166
(Elizabeth)
We tried the trailer park,
he wasn't there.

13:21.168 --> 13:23.735
So he's not with
his usual associates

13:23.737 --> 13:25.103
and we know from the
Highway Patrol

13:25.105 --> 13:26.204
that he hasn't
left the state.

13:26.206 --> 13:29.340
Yeah, what other place
would matter to him?

13:29.342 --> 13:33.278
What about the place where
his little brother died?

13:33.280 --> 13:34.979
The Weldon warehouse.

13:34.981 --> 13:37.415
Truck exploded and he
was held responsible

13:37.417 --> 13:40.351
even though he wasn't.

13:40.353 --> 13:42.153
Where is this
Weldon warehouse?

13:42.155 --> 13:45.290
It's about, uh,
a half-hour maybe.

13:45.292 --> 13:46.057
Okay, I'm there.

13:46.059 --> 13:47.926
You know what, I'm gonna
check the chop shops.

13:47.928 --> 13:48.993
Maybe he traded
his car in.

13:48.995 --> 13:50.762
All right,
we'll meet back here.

13:50.764 --> 13:52.430
Okay.

13:53.465 --> 13:54.132
(knocking)

13:54.134 --> 13:57.402
(David)
Grant, are you in there?

14:06.712 --> 14:10.148
You wanna play?

14:10.150 --> 14:12.083
You know how?

14:12.085 --> 14:13.351
No idea.

14:13.353 --> 14:15.820
So, guarantees
you'll win.

14:25.764 --> 14:28.433
(gunshots)

14:31.770 --> 14:35.173
Uh, which one
are we?

14:35.175 --> 14:37.542
You're the dead one.

14:41.981 --> 14:45.884
Maybe if you teach me,
it'll be more fun.

14:50.322 --> 14:51.089
Doubt it.

14:51.091 --> 14:54.792
Aw, come on,
I'm a quick learner.

14:59.331 --> 15:01.232
(sighs)

15:01.234 --> 15:03.334
This is how you shoot.

15:03.336 --> 15:05.036
This is how
you move around.

15:05.038 --> 15:09.073
Okay, and what about that?

15:09.075 --> 15:12.977
That's to pause
the game, Dad.

15:12.979 --> 15:15.813
Okay, I'm good.

15:22.721 --> 15:24.222
No, Max's mom
is in there.

15:24.224 --> 15:27.425
Karen's here?
Can we talk?

15:29.295 --> 15:30.194
What?

15:30.196 --> 15:31.930
Were you and Max
in love?

15:31.932 --> 15:33.765
What are you
talking about?

15:33.767 --> 15:36.334
It's all Karen could
talk about was you and Max.

15:36.336 --> 15:41.072
Taylor, Karen doesn't know
what she's saying, come on.

15:41.074 --> 15:43.274
Carter,
Karen loves you.

15:43.276 --> 15:44.242
And I defended you.

15:44.244 --> 15:46.945
I said it wasn't your
fault that Max got shot,

15:46.947 --> 15:48.046
but everyone
knows it was.

15:48.048 --> 15:50.214
Okay, well, Taylor,
you don't have to say

15:50.216 --> 15:52.150
anything to Karen about me,
all right?

15:52.152 --> 15:53.217
I'm gonna explain it.

15:53.219 --> 15:55.820
Yeah, explain how it
was an accident.

15:55.822 --> 15:57.488
It wasn't my
boyfriend's fault.

15:57.490 --> 15:59.424
His life story
is so sad.

15:59.426 --> 16:02.794
What parent wouldn't
love to hear that?

16:02.796 --> 16:05.463
(phone buzzing)

16:08.400 --> 16:12.036
It's Elizabeth,
I have to take this.

16:20.212 --> 16:23.281
(sighing)
Crash.

16:23.283 --> 16:24.983
Hey, where are you?

16:24.985 --> 16:25.750
The hospital.

16:25.752 --> 16:28.419
I'm going back in to
see Max, stop calling me.

16:28.421 --> 16:30.421
<i>Carter, wait.</i>

16:38.797 --> 16:40.932
(glass shattering)

16:46.772 --> 16:49.440
Clear the hallway!

16:49.442 --> 16:52.777
(man)
Watch your back.

16:52.779 --> 16:54.746
Max, baby.
I'm sorry.

16:54.748 --> 16:55.813
(Carter)
What's happening?

16:55.815 --> 16:58.116
It's his heart,
it's something with his heart.

16:58.118 --> 17:00.151
(Nurse)
He's going into surgery,
you need to wait here.

17:00.153 --> 17:04.722
As soon if we find something
out, we'll let you know.

17:11.663 --> 17:13.731
Crash?

17:18.804 --> 17:22.073
Listen,
I've seen the truck.

17:26.045 --> 17:28.913
It's just me.

17:32.751 --> 17:37.855
Listen, I know how hard it is
to turn your life around.

17:39.892 --> 17:42.026
You can do this.

17:47.066 --> 17:51.235
Crash, you can do
the right thing.

17:52.404 --> 17:55.773
(phone buzzing)

17:57.743 --> 17:59.844
♪

18:16.161 --> 18:19.030
Hi, um-- oh,
they're there.

18:19.032 --> 18:20.498
Hey.

18:20.500 --> 18:21.833
What's going on?

18:21.835 --> 18:24.035
Rich, don't make me
do this alone.

18:24.037 --> 18:25.303
He's in the hospital.

18:25.305 --> 18:26.471
Max's mom?
Yeah.

18:26.473 --> 18:29.373
What did the doctor say?
This is really serious.

18:29.375 --> 18:31.843
Something cardiac.

18:31.845 --> 18:34.312
She was too upset
to listen.
Yeah.

18:34.314 --> 18:36.747
Okay, let me see
what I can find out.

18:36.749 --> 18:38.316
I'll be right back.

18:38.318 --> 18:40.485
Great, I've hit
my data limit.

18:40.487 --> 18:43.221
I can't send
any more texts.

18:43.223 --> 18:44.255
Stupid phone.

18:44.257 --> 18:46.057
Karen, look, here.

18:46.059 --> 18:47.859
You can use mine.

18:50.129 --> 18:51.562
Carter.

18:55.434 --> 18:57.435
I knew you
weren't responsible

18:57.437 --> 19:00.371
for what happened,
okay?

19:00.373 --> 19:01.472
As soon as I heard,
I knew

19:01.474 --> 19:05.510
no matter what went on,
it wasn't your fault.

19:05.512 --> 19:07.845
I mean, you stayed
with him, right?

19:07.847 --> 19:09.480
You called 911.

19:09.482 --> 19:12.250
What would Max do
without you?

19:12.252 --> 19:14.051
You've taken such
good care of him

19:14.053 --> 19:15.353
since he's been here.

19:15.355 --> 19:16.220
(sniffling)

19:16.222 --> 19:19.824
He was so excited
to move down here

19:19.826 --> 19:21.292
and see you.

19:21.294 --> 19:22.927
(chuckles)

19:23.896 --> 19:26.931
You have been such
an important influence

19:26.933 --> 19:27.465
in his life.

19:27.467 --> 19:30.168
I'm going to the
vending machines.

19:30.170 --> 19:33.271
You were so
important to him.

19:34.206 --> 19:36.240
Carter, where's Taylor?

19:36.242 --> 19:37.875
Taylor.

19:37.877 --> 19:39.010
This is what
I found out.

19:39.012 --> 19:41.946
Even though the bullet
missed Max's heart,

19:41.948 --> 19:45.216
it's still not functioning
the way it should.

19:45.218 --> 19:46.484
(sighs)

19:46.486 --> 19:47.818
What?

19:47.820 --> 19:49.987
Well-- Well,
can they fix it?

19:49.989 --> 19:51.756
I don't know.
He's still in surgery.

19:51.758 --> 19:54.792
But they promised me that
we could talk to the doctor

19:54.794 --> 19:57.361
as soon as he comes out.

19:57.363 --> 19:59.096
Karen?

19:59.098 --> 20:00.398
Hi, I'm Elizabeth.

20:00.400 --> 20:01.199
I'm the girl's mom.

20:01.201 --> 20:04.435
I just wanted to
let you know that Max,

20:04.437 --> 20:05.469
he's like a member
of our family,

20:05.471 --> 20:09.240
and he is getting the best care
in the world right now,

20:09.242 --> 20:10.041
I promise you.

20:10.043 --> 20:12.009
And I am doing
everything I can

20:12.011 --> 20:14.212
to apprehend the kid
that did this.

20:14.214 --> 20:16.881
Your Carter's
real mom.

20:18.450 --> 20:20.618
(whispering)
Yeah.

20:23.922 --> 20:25.890
(sobbing)

20:25.892 --> 20:28.492
(Elizabeth)
I know. It's okay.

20:28.494 --> 20:30.828
It's okay.

20:30.830 --> 20:31.996
It's okay.

20:31.998 --> 20:34.365
(phone buzzing)

20:36.368 --> 20:42.506
♪ I've gone on
too long ♪

20:43.342 --> 20:47.011
Come on, pick up,
pick up, pick up, pick up.

20:48.914 --> 20:50.314
♪ ...This heart of stone

20:50.316 --> 20:53.384
(train whistle blowing)

20:53.386 --> 20:58.189
♪ Just let me go

21:01.293 --> 21:04.128
♪ Just let me go

21:04.130 --> 21:06.597
Still not talking
to Bird?

21:07.366 --> 21:09.100
No, I'm not.
Why not?

21:09.102 --> 21:12.103
She seems to wanna
make up with you.

21:12.105 --> 21:13.404
Well, that's between
me and Bird.

21:13.406 --> 21:15.506
Why do you think
you're the only one

21:15.508 --> 21:17.842
who's allowed
to be upset?

21:18.477 --> 21:21.912
Is this because of what Karen
said about me and Max?

21:21.914 --> 21:23.214
Excuse me?

21:23.216 --> 21:25.449
You have no reason
to be jealous.

21:25.451 --> 21:27.952
You are his girlfriend,
and he loves you.

21:27.954 --> 21:28.853
Who said I was jealous?

21:28.855 --> 21:32.056
He can't hate me because
she still cares about me.

21:32.058 --> 21:34.925
I'm the only one
she knows here.

21:35.027 --> 21:38.062
I can't believe you
just said that, Carter.

21:39.965 --> 21:42.066
You are a mess!

21:42.068 --> 21:47.471
Seriously,
you are such a mess.

21:50.142 --> 21:51.442
Thanks, Taylor.

21:51.444 --> 21:53.010
Sure.
Thank you.

21:53.012 --> 21:55.980
Yeah, I am a mess
right now. I am.

21:55.982 --> 21:59.450
I am a mess because my
best friend just got shot,

21:59.452 --> 22:02.219
because my boyfriend was
the one who shot him,

22:02.221 --> 22:03.387
because my friend
betrayed me,

22:03.389 --> 22:07.992
and now, because
my sister hates me.

22:09.795 --> 22:10.861
(sighs)

22:10.863 --> 22:13.798
I am trying to make
this all better.

22:13.800 --> 22:15.833
(phone buzzing)

22:15.835 --> 22:17.101
(sniffling)

22:17.103 --> 22:19.503
Well, you need to
figure it out.

22:19.505 --> 22:22.039
Max is out of surgery.

22:22.041 --> 22:22.973
What?

22:22.975 --> 22:24.842
Now, Carter.

22:24.844 --> 22:27.878
You guys.

22:33.251 --> 22:35.319
And they can become
very complicated.

22:35.321 --> 22:37.521
I don't understand,
you're saying he had
a heart attack?

22:37.523 --> 22:39.990
It's what's known as
a cardiac tamponade.

22:39.992 --> 22:42.093
Blood began pooling
in the pericardium--

22:42.095 --> 22:43.160
it's a sac around
his heart--

22:43.162 --> 22:44.495
putting pressure on it
so that it couldn't pump.

22:44.497 --> 22:47.832
His blood pressure dropped
and his body went into shock.

22:47.834 --> 22:49.934
We were able to cut
a window in the sac

22:49.936 --> 22:50.534
and allow it to drain.

22:50.536 --> 22:53.471
So his heart is
functioning normally now.

22:53.473 --> 22:55.072
It's functioning
normally, yes.

22:55.074 --> 22:57.842
He's still
non-responsive?

22:57.844 --> 22:58.442
That hasn't changed.

22:58.444 --> 23:00.578
And do we know when
he's gonna wake up?

23:00.580 --> 23:03.280
No, I'm sorry.

23:03.282 --> 23:04.081
We're in a waiting game.

23:04.083 --> 23:05.783
Okay, that is
the exact same thing

23:05.785 --> 23:06.350
you said last night.

23:06.352 --> 23:08.753
Carter, it's okay,
we will handle it.

23:08.755 --> 23:10.988
We cannot
handle this.

23:10.990 --> 23:13.157
I can't handle this.

23:13.159 --> 23:15.292
We're gonna get
through this, okay?

23:15.294 --> 23:18.429
But, we have to
be strong for Max.

23:18.431 --> 23:20.064
Okay?

23:25.771 --> 23:27.938
Okay, for Max.

23:27.940 --> 23:31.776
♪ Help, help
I'm drowning ♪

23:31.778 --> 23:35.179
♪ In the sea
where I found you ♪

23:35.181 --> 23:38.315
♪ The kerosene
in your skin ♪

23:38.317 --> 23:41.552
♪ The chemistry
that I'm bound to ♪

23:41.554 --> 23:46.857
♪ Thought I drew out
the cancers... ♪

23:46.859 --> 23:49.059
DNA, fingerprints,
anything?

23:49.061 --> 23:51.262
Damn.

23:51.264 --> 23:55.099
I just knew that
he was there.

23:55.101 --> 24:00.070
♪

24:00.072 --> 24:01.071
Psst.

24:01.073 --> 24:04.008
Hi. You know,
I forgot to ask you,

24:04.010 --> 24:05.910
how did that
job interview go?

24:05.912 --> 24:08.946
Oh, I forgot, too.
I got it.

24:08.948 --> 24:10.147
You got it?
Yes.

24:10.149 --> 24:12.183
Fantastic.
congratulations!

24:12.185 --> 24:13.250
Thank you.

24:13.252 --> 24:14.018
Where?

24:14.020 --> 24:16.120
McAllister Holt Academy.

24:16.122 --> 24:17.354
(Ofe)
Really?

24:17.356 --> 24:20.357
I used to go there,
once upon a time.

24:20.359 --> 24:21.459
It's a great school.

24:21.461 --> 24:23.060
I was-- I was
kicked out,

24:23.062 --> 24:28.532
uh, for a minor infraction
I don't do no more.

24:30.101 --> 24:32.837
Anyway...
That's great, Dad,

24:32.839 --> 24:34.138
I'm happy for you.

24:34.140 --> 24:35.906
Thank you,
sweetie.

24:35.908 --> 24:39.376
Congratulations.

24:41.112 --> 24:43.047
Thank you.

24:54.359 --> 24:56.861
You know, Karen, um...

24:56.863 --> 24:59.930
Taylor's been taking
care of Max's plants

24:59.932 --> 25:01.966
all this time.

25:03.001 --> 25:05.169
Thank you.

25:06.137 --> 25:07.805
He loves
his plants.

25:07.807 --> 25:10.474
The blooms came in
on his hibiscus.

25:10.476 --> 25:12.209
He's gonna
be so excited.

25:12.211 --> 25:14.812
Well, that boy
is never happier

25:14.814 --> 25:16.247
than when he has
some dirt

25:16.249 --> 25:18.015
and a new
package of seeds.

25:18.017 --> 25:19.984
Except when he's
making croutons.

25:19.986 --> 25:21.952
He makes croutons?
Mm-hmm,

25:21.954 --> 25:22.953
Taylor taught him.

25:22.955 --> 25:24.488
He's really
good at it.

25:24.490 --> 25:25.422
Oh, my gosh.

25:25.424 --> 25:27.992
Well, if you
aren't the sweetest.

25:27.994 --> 25:32.296
She is, Karen.
She's the sweetest.

25:32.298 --> 25:34.064
Max really loves her.

25:34.066 --> 25:37.101
Well, I can
certainly see why.

25:37.103 --> 25:40.137
He's so kind
and soulful.

25:40.139 --> 25:42.373
And those are two words
that I don't use much.

25:42.375 --> 25:47.111
Basically, it's impossible
not to like the guy.

25:47.113 --> 25:49.346
(Ofe)
He's great.
He's at the top of my

25:49.348 --> 25:51.515
"if I could be anybody
in the world" list.

25:51.517 --> 25:54.818
Like, above Beyonce.

25:54.820 --> 25:56.520
Oh.
(laughing)

25:58.356 --> 26:01.258
Yeah, he-- he's like
a brother to me.

26:01.860 --> 26:05.162
Well, he always
wanted a brother, so...

26:05.164 --> 26:10.200
I was-- I was
just too young.

26:10.202 --> 26:13.804
We could tell you about all
the funny and great things

26:13.806 --> 26:15.973
Max has done
since he's been here.

26:15.975 --> 26:17.441
Like--
Laundry?

26:17.443 --> 26:19.910
Yeah.
Yes.

26:19.912 --> 26:20.711
You let him
do laundry?

26:20.713 --> 26:24.148
Okay, you guys know all
the shirts that he wears

26:24.150 --> 26:25.149
that are the same color?

26:25.151 --> 26:28.052
They did not
start out that way.

26:28.054 --> 26:30.054
That's why I'm
wearing black.

26:30.056 --> 26:32.089
(laughter)

26:47.138 --> 26:50.374
(sighing)
You can't avoid me forever.

26:58.249 --> 27:00.117
Fine.

27:01.786 --> 27:06.323
I don't know if you're
gonna understand this, but...

27:06.325 --> 27:11.362
I'm terrified
of my parents.

27:11.364 --> 27:14.932
Elizabeth isn't exactly
a walk in the park.

27:14.934 --> 27:18.802
But at least you know
she loves you.

27:18.804 --> 27:21.772
I don't even know
if my mom likes me.

27:21.774 --> 27:25.242
And my dad is definitely
not interested.

27:25.244 --> 27:30.047
I know, who doesn't have
self-esteem issues, right?

27:30.049 --> 27:32.783
Well, besides you.

27:32.785 --> 27:36.153
Um, I have
self-esteem issues.

27:36.155 --> 27:40.824
Well, if you do, they're
practically invisible because...

27:40.826 --> 27:43.761
you're the girl who
everybody wants to know,

27:43.763 --> 27:47.831
and who everybody
wants to be with.

27:47.833 --> 27:50.801
I made a mistake.

27:50.803 --> 27:55.205
A really, really
vicious mistake.

27:56.107 --> 27:58.242
And now, my parents
are making whispers

27:58.244 --> 28:01.412
about boarding school.

28:01.414 --> 28:03.414
(sighing)

28:03.416 --> 28:07.084
I'm sorry
to hear that.

28:08.119 --> 28:10.187
Well...

28:10.189 --> 28:14.358
you gotta pay for
your mistakes, right?

28:17.095 --> 28:19.263
Are you still in
touch with him?

28:22.300 --> 28:25.202
Carter, I don't know if
you're ever gonna forgive me,

28:25.204 --> 28:30.441
but I'm just trying to be
a real friend for you now.

28:31.843 --> 28:35.145
I'm happy Crash is
out of my life.

28:35.147 --> 28:38.949
But, I really think you
need to get him out of yours.

28:38.951 --> 28:42.553
♪

28:57.302 --> 29:00.304
(phone line ringing)

29:00.306 --> 29:02.272
(Crash)
<i>Carter.</i>

29:05.376 --> 29:07.077
Carter, is it you?

29:07.079 --> 29:09.246
Yeah, it's me.

29:09.248 --> 29:10.414
Why didn't you
pick up the phone?

29:10.416 --> 29:11.348
Why didn't you answer
my texts?

29:11.350 --> 29:14.351
<i>I told you,</i>
<i>I'm at the hospital.</i>

29:14.353 --> 29:16.854
Are you okay?
<i>No.</i>

29:16.856 --> 29:18.856
Elizabeth, she was
at the place today.

29:18.858 --> 29:20.057
She almost caught me.

29:20.059 --> 29:21.291
Now it's like every
time I turn around,

29:21.293 --> 29:23.393
she's gonna be
right behind me.

29:23.395 --> 29:24.561
She's not, okay?

29:24.563 --> 29:26.497
She's at the hospital,
you can relax.

29:26.499 --> 29:28.999
Okay, all right,
but I have to leave tonight.

29:29.001 --> 29:30.400
I-- I need to see you.

29:30.402 --> 29:32.903
Crash, we're waiting
to see if Max wakes up.

29:32.905 --> 29:34.938
<i>All right, well, I have</i>
<i>to leave by midnight,</i>

29:34.940 --> 29:36.006
no later than that.

29:36.008 --> 29:38.242
I'll be at the water tower.

29:38.244 --> 29:39.543
I can't.

29:39.545 --> 29:42.880
Carter, please.

29:45.316 --> 29:47.084
(sighs)

29:48.119 --> 29:50.354
All right, fine,
I'll come.

29:50.356 --> 29:53.957
Okay.

29:57.529 --> 30:00.531
Carter... wait.

30:00.533 --> 30:03.867
Guys, I have been
in there for hours.

30:03.869 --> 30:04.568
I just need a break.

30:04.570 --> 30:06.103
I need to go get, like,

30:06.105 --> 30:07.437
a burger and fries
or something.

30:07.439 --> 30:11.041
That sounds great, I could go
for a burger and fries.

30:11.043 --> 30:12.943
Is she really going for a
burger and fries right now?

30:12.945 --> 30:14.411
No, she's not really going
for a burger and fries--

30:14.413 --> 30:15.913
(Gabe)
Where's she going, Bird?

30:15.915 --> 30:17.447
Where am I
going, Bird?

30:17.449 --> 30:19.516
To see Crash?

30:19.518 --> 30:24.154
Look, Carter, he's obviously
a very unstable person.

30:24.156 --> 30:26.156
You can't go near him.

30:26.158 --> 30:28.258
He--

30:28.260 --> 30:29.960
He just wants
to say good-bye.

30:29.962 --> 30:30.627
(Bird)
You can't go!

30:30.629 --> 30:32.796
Carter, if I can see that
he's scum, how can you not?

30:32.798 --> 30:37.201
Guys, he is not some,
like, crazy, evil villain.

30:37.203 --> 30:38.902
He is just a guy who did

30:38.904 --> 30:41.505
a really,
really stupid thing.

30:41.507 --> 30:43.640
And now, he is scared
and alone,

30:43.642 --> 30:46.410
and he has no one
in the world to help him.

30:46.412 --> 30:49.012
Well, you have to
cut him loose.

30:49.014 --> 30:51.782
Gabe's right, he's just
gonna drag you down.

30:51.784 --> 30:52.916
He already has.

30:52.918 --> 30:54.852
I-- I can't
deal with this.

30:54.854 --> 30:55.953
I have to sort this out.

30:55.955 --> 31:00.023
Carter, just don't do
anything stupid, okay?

31:00.025 --> 31:02.960
(sighs)
For once, right?

31:02.962 --> 31:09.132
♪

31:40.365 --> 31:41.999
You came.

31:42.001 --> 31:43.600
Why did you run?

31:43.602 --> 31:46.436
Why did I run?

31:46.438 --> 31:48.272
I couldn't just
stand there.

31:48.274 --> 31:49.406
Was I supposed
to wait around?

31:49.408 --> 31:53.543
I-- I couldn't,
I couldn't stay.

31:53.545 --> 31:56.146
I'm sorry.

31:56.148 --> 31:58.482
I told you,
I was sorry.

31:58.484 --> 32:00.951
Yeah, I believe you.

32:00.953 --> 32:03.387
I got rid of the gun.

32:03.389 --> 32:05.555
Threw it out.

32:07.425 --> 32:12.129
Let's sit, let's sit--
No, no, no.

32:12.131 --> 32:13.897
No, I need the fresh air.

32:13.899 --> 32:15.399
It's a long drive
to California.

32:15.401 --> 32:17.935
You're still going
to California?

32:17.937 --> 32:19.603
Yeah.

32:19.605 --> 32:22.906
That was our plan,
remember?

32:22.908 --> 32:25.075
Crash, if you stayed,

32:25.077 --> 32:28.412
you could tell everyone
it was a mistake.

32:28.414 --> 32:29.279
I would support you.

32:29.281 --> 32:32.015
It's not like
you'd be doing it
on your own.

32:32.017 --> 32:32.883
The thing is, Carter,

32:32.885 --> 32:36.887
I'm not so sure
that it was a mistake.

32:36.889 --> 32:38.522
What do you mean?

32:38.524 --> 32:44.328
Listen, I didn't mean
to shoot Max, I didn't.

32:44.330 --> 32:45.629
But I shot him.

32:45.631 --> 32:47.664
Before I shot him,
I was sitting in the truck,

32:47.666 --> 32:50.267
and I was watching
you two touching

32:50.269 --> 32:51.368
and hugging and stuff.

32:51.370 --> 32:54.204
Yeah, me and Max are friends,
we do that all the time.

32:54.206 --> 32:57.341
Yeah, and that
pisses me off.

32:57.343 --> 32:59.443
When I was in juvie,
they told me I--

32:59.445 --> 33:02.846
I had these triggers
I needed to work on...

33:02.848 --> 33:04.614
impulse control.

33:06.217 --> 33:08.285
You should have
told me that.

33:08.287 --> 33:11.054
I told you.

33:12.490 --> 33:13.623
I warned you.

33:13.625 --> 33:15.392
The first day
I told you,

33:15.394 --> 33:18.362
I destroy everything.

33:22.233 --> 33:24.334
No, Crash.

33:24.336 --> 33:26.436
No, please.
Crash.

33:33.044 --> 33:37.948
You want so much to believe
that you're a bad person.

33:39.517 --> 33:42.419
But, I don't buy it.

33:44.222 --> 33:46.289
I don't.

33:46.291 --> 33:49.192
You'll never
convince me.

33:50.528 --> 33:53.263
I was there.

33:53.265 --> 33:56.600
It was an accident,
I saw it.

33:57.635 --> 34:01.271
God, I can't believe I'm
never gonna see you again.

34:02.340 --> 34:04.941
You don't know that.

34:04.943 --> 34:08.478
You remember the first
time you kissed me?

34:08.480 --> 34:12.516
It was so ballsy, it was
right in front of Elizabeth.

34:13.184 --> 34:15.252
The way that
you looked at me,

34:15.254 --> 34:19.056
you looked into my eyes,
I'll never forget it.

34:21.893 --> 34:24.094
See, there it is.

34:26.931 --> 34:28.198
This is love, this--

34:28.200 --> 34:31.101
This is that
unbearable feeling that...

34:31.103 --> 34:34.404
(sighing)
... never goes away.

34:39.010 --> 34:43.380
Why do people want
to feel like this?

34:43.382 --> 34:46.316
I don't know.

34:48.386 --> 34:50.854
(police siren blaring)

34:50.856 --> 34:56.026
♪ If I was not myself

34:56.028 --> 34:57.494
♪ And you were...

34:57.496 --> 34:59.563
No.
Crash.

35:01.299 --> 35:02.432
Crash, let me see your hands!

35:02.434 --> 35:05.602
Put your hands...
Get your...

35:05.604 --> 35:08.905
(whispering)
I'm sorry.

35:08.907 --> 35:11.575
Get her away
from here, now!

35:11.577 --> 35:13.076
Crash.
Come on.

